pr_body:
When dealing with images for deep learning, it is often useful to normalise them first.

This PR introduces a new pixel type rgb_normalized_pixel which makes it easy to deal with colour values centered at 0 (+/- 0.5)

Loading an image which is normalised is as easy as:
```
matrix<rgb_normalized_pixel> image;
load_image(image, "test.png");
// And this can be directly saved too
save_png(image, "rgb-norm.png");
save_bmp(image, "rgb-norm.bmp");
save_jpeg(image, "rgb-norm.jpg");
// save_dng(image, "rgb-norm.dng"); <= This is broken currently
```

@davisking I have tried to add some tests but this PR will benefit from your more thorough look through. Currently save_dng is broken. This will also be useful later when/if we want to expose normalised images to Python in a queue or some other mechanism.

